~ comments are invisible to every renderer.

~ two forms:
~   ~ at the start of a line       — the rest of the line is a comment
~   ~~ ... ~~/                      — inline, may span lines.
~                                     the tail wraps it up.

~ rules:
~   ~~ always opens an inline comment, even at line start.
~   ~ followed by whitespace at line start opens a line comment.
~   ~~/ closes an inline comment. plain ~~ inside an open comment is
~       just content, so the writer can use it as a divider however
~       they like.


~ line comments

~ remember to verify this date before publishing
The lighthouse was commissioned in 1847.

~ TODO: confirm the year of the new bell
He served thirty-one years.


~ inline comments

The bell ~~ TODO: confirm year ~~/ rang on the hour.

The keeper, Aldous Vane ~~ check spelling against the parish record ~~/, was thirty-one years at post.


~ multi-line inline

~~ a longer aside:
   we should decide whether epigraphs count toward the chapter's
   word count. for now they don't. ~~/

For eleven days the lamp had burned untended.


~ internal ~~ as a free divider

~~ TODO ~~ also fix the typo on page 3 ~~ and verify the footnote ~~/

~~ note ~~ rough draft ~~ needs editor pass ~~/

~~ section one ~~ section two ~~ section three ~~/


~ what does NOT trigger a comment

~ a tilde attached to a token is just a tilde.
The crossing took ~5 minutes.
He smiled ~half-heartedly~ at the lamp.
The estimate, x ~ y, held within tolerance.

~ shell paths inside comments are safe — ~~/ is the close, not ~/.
~~ TODO: save the file to ~/Documents/notes and ~/.bashrc ~~/

~ the close fires anywhere — end of line, mid-line, doesn't matter.
~~ aside that ends mid-line ~~/ and then prose resumes.
